# .claude/.gitignore
# Controls what gets committed to the repository vs. kept local

# ============================================================================
# COMMIT POLICY (What we DO commit):
# ============================================================================
# - Core architectural docs: CLAUDE.md, EXTENSIONS_VISION.md, ARCHITECTURE.md, etc.
# - API reference materials: api-spec/
# - Default slash commands: commands/spy/*.md
# - This README and .gitignore
#
# These are stable project knowledge that benefits all contributors.

# ============================================================================
# IGNORE POLICY (What we DON'T commit):
# ============================================================================

# Session-specific notes and context
SESSION_*.md
temporal-context/
snapshots/

# Exploratory and brainstorming notes
roadmap-brainstorms/

# Learning notes and scratchpads
*LEARNING*.md
*PRICING*.md

# Session helpers (regenerated per-session)
QUICK_REFERENCE.md
START_HERE.md

# Temporal planning documents
RELEASE_PLAN*.md

# User-specific overrides and local state
*.local.md
*.local.json
.state/
.cache/

# Future: User hooks will live here (always ignored)
# See EXTENSIONS_VISION.md Phase 4
hooks/
examples/hooks/*.sh

# Editor temp files (belt-and-suspenders, also in root .gitignore)
*.swp
*.swo
*~
